NASA GEO Peru Workshop

About

Date: 19 August 2019
By: Patrick Burns, Patrick Jantz, and J. Camilo Fagua
Contact: Patrick.Burns@nau.edu, Patrick.Jantz@nau.edu, Camilo.Fagua@nau.edu

Acronyms:
ALS = Airborne Laser Scanner
GEDI = Global Ecosystem Dynamics Investigation

About the data:
Airborne lidar data provided by Sustainable Landscapes Brazil - please do NOT redistribute
Data access: https://www.paisagenslidar.cnptia.embrapa.br/webgis/

Airborne lidar data were simulated to produce GEDI lidar 25 m footprints
Note: GEDI is scheduled for launch and installation in early December 2018

Learning Goals

  1. Understand the difference between airborne lidar and waveform lidar data
  2. Use open-source R packages to visualize and manipulate airborne lidar data in 2D and 3D
  3. Visually compare airborne lidar point clouds with simulated GEDI waveforms
  4. Produce average relative height profiles and waveforms for area in this example

Part 1: Data Import

First download the data from the dropbox link shared in the workshop

Load in airborne lidar data (this is the file with .laz extension)
Supply the file path in the variable lidar_ALS_file
Then read in the data with lidR::readLAS

lidar_ALS_file='D:/lidar/data/ex1_data/JAML4980C8990.laz'
lidar_ALS_data=lidR::readLAS(files = lidar_ALS_file)
# Specify the projection string associated with the ALS lidar data  
projStr = "+proj=utm +zone=20 +south +ellps=GRS80 +towgs84=0,0,0,0,0,0,0 +units=m +no_defs"

Load in spaceborne GEDI lidar simulated data (this is the file with .csv extension)
Note: The GEDI footprints should overlap with airborne lidar data
Supply the file path in the variable lidar_GEDI_file

lidar_GEDI_file='D:/lidar/data/ex1_data/GEDI_L2_embrapa_brazil_keller_2013_32720_subset.csv'

Vertical complexity
Note:Vertical complexity metrics summarize variation in vertical canopy structure
lidR allows the user to calculate custom metrics for each grid cell using a pre-defined function:

zMetrics = function(z){
  # Calculate Shannon's diversity index on normalized heights
  # First make a histogram
  vertBinSize = 1 # vertical bin width in meters
  vs <- floor(min(z)/10)*10
  vf <- ceiling(max(z)/10)*10
  if (vf-vs==0) {
    shan <- 0
  } else {
    h = hist(z, breaks = seq(vs,vf,vertBinSize), plot=FALSE)
    h_df = data.frame(h$mids)
    h_df$counts = h$counts
    h_df$dens = h$density
    # remove 0 values which will cause an error with Shannon's diversity
    h_df = h_df[h_df$counts>0,]
    # loop through each height bin
    v = vector("numeric", nrow(h_df))
    for (i in 1:nrow(h_df)){
      p = h_df$dens[i]
      s = p*log(p)
      v[i] = s
    }
    # Calculate Shannon's diversity
    shan = -1*sum(v)
    vtop = tail(v, n=1)
    vbottom = v[1]
  }
  # These are the metrics to output
  metrics = list( 
    z_sd = sd(z), # standard deviation of normalized heights
    z_cv = cv(z), # coefficient of variation of normalized heights
    z_shan = shan, # Shannon's diversity index
    z_50 = quantile(z, 0.5), # Calculate 50th percentile of heights
    z_98 = quantile(z, 0.98), # Calculate 98th percentile of heights
    z_100 = quantile(z, 1) # Calculate 100th percentile of heights
  )
  return(metrics)
}
# Calculate the custom vertical complexity metrics
lidar_ALS_zComp = lidR::grid_metrics(Normal_lidar_ALS_data, zMetrics(Z), res = 2)
plot(lidar_ALS_zComp)

PART 4: Overlap airborne lidar with GEDI footprints

First make the point geometry for the simulated GEDI footprint centers Note: X-Y coordinates are contained in the GEDI simulation (.csv) file

xycols = c("lon","lat")
lidar_GEDI_pts = sp::SpatialPointsDataFrame(coords = lidar_GEDI_data[,xycols], data = lidar_GEDI_data)
# Specify the projection of the points
crs(lidar_GEDI_pts) = projStr
# Only select GEDI points that fall within the lidarboundary  
lidar_GEDI_pts = lidar_GEDI_pts[lidar_ALS_box,]
# Make a column of unique IDs for each GEDI observation and add to the data frame  
lidar_GEDI_pts$ID = seq(1,nrow(lidar_GEDI_pts),1)

Buffer the selected GEDI points to create a circular footprint geometry.
Specify the buffer radius in meters. Note: GEDI footprints will have a 25m diameter

buffDist = 12.5 

lidar_GEDI_Bpts = rgeos::gBuffer(spgeom = lidar_GEDI_pts, width = buffDist, byid = TRUE)
lidar_GEDI_Bpts = SpatialPolygonsDataFrame(lidar_GEDI_Bpts, data = lidar_GEDI_pts@data)

Plot the airborne lidar canopy height model with the buffered GEDI points

plot(lidar_ALS_chm, main = "ALS Canopy Height Model with GEDI footprints", col = grey.colors(20))

# Label the GEDI footprints with their ID number
rgeos::polygonsLabel(pols = lidar_GEDI_Bpts, labels = lidar_GEDI_Bpts$ID, 
                     method = 'centroid', cex = 0.5, col = "black")

Part 5: Plotting Individual GEDI waveforms

You can try repeating this part of the exercise for different GEDI footprints

GEDI level 2 (L2) simulated data only contain relative height (RH) values
We need to invert the L2 GEDI relative heights to a waveform

Specify a GEDI footprint ID number in the variable GEDI_FP_ID below and run the entire code block

GEDI_FP_ID = '27'

# Specify the re-binning size (in meters) for the GEDI waveform
binSize = 2
# Extract simulated GEDI data for footprint of interest
GEDI_FP = subset(lidar_GEDI_Bpts, ID %in% GEDI_FP_ID)
GEDI_FP_DF = GEDI_FP@data
GEDI_FP_RH = as.data.frame(t(GEDI_FP_DF[ , grepl( "rhReal" , names( GEDI_FP_DF ) ) ]))
colnames(GEDI_FP_RH) = c("RH")
GEDI_FP_RH$binCuml = seq(0,100,2)
GEDI_FP_RH$binPerc = 2
# Re-bin the relative height values into new bins
binsBig = seq(-100, 100, binSize)
rh = vector("numeric")
en = vector("numeric")
interv = vector("numeric")
for (i in 1:(nrow(GEDI_FP_RH)-1)){
    start = length(rh)+1
    binsSmall = seq(GEDI_FP_RH$RH[i], GEDI_FP_RH$RH[i+1], 0.1)
    len = length(binsSmall)
    end = (start+len)-1
    rh[start:end] = binsSmall
    en[start:end] = 2/length(binsSmall)
    interv[start:end] = findInterval(x = rh[start:end], vec = binsBig)
}
# Combine the re-binned data into a data frame
lidar_GEDI_preWave = data.frame(rh, en, interv)
lidar_GEDI_preWave$binsBig = binsBig[interv]
lidar_GEDI_wave = aggregate(lidar_GEDI_preWave$en, by=list(Category=lidar_GEDI_preWave$binsBig), FUN=sum)
colnames(lidar_GEDI_wave) = c("zBin", "percEnergy")
# Extract the airborne lidar points corresponding to this GEDI footprint
GEDI_FP_poly = GEDI_FP@polygons[[1]]@Polygons[[1]]
lidar_ALS_GEDI_FP = lasclip(Normal_lidar_ALS_data, GEDI_FP_poly, ofile = "")
# Make a 2D plot of the points within one GEDI footprint. Plot a cross-section (X vs Z)
# First need to calculate histograms of point distributions for X and Z dimensions
h1 <- hist(lidar_ALS_GEDI_FP@data$X, breaks=10, plot=F)
h2 <- hist(lidar_ALS_GEDI_FP@data$Z, breaks=20, plot=F)
top <- max(h1$counts, h2$counts)
# Make the 2d plot for one footprint

oldpar <- par()
par(mar=c(5,5,1,0))

layout(matrix(c(2,5,6,1,3,4),2,3,byrow=T),c(3,1), c(1,3))
plot(lidar_ALS_GEDI_FP@data$X, lidar_ALS_GEDI_FP@data$Z, 
     pch=16, col = rgb(0.2, 0.9, 0.2, 0.2),
     xlim = c(min(lidar_ALS_GEDI_FP@data$X), max(lidar_ALS_GEDI_FP@data$X)), 
     ylim = c(min(lidar_ALS_GEDI_FP@data$Z), max(lidar_ALS_GEDI_FP@data$Z)),
     xlab = "X (m)",
     ylab = "Height Above Ground, Z (m)")
par(mar=c(0.1,5,1,0))
barplot(h1$counts, axes=F, 
        xlim = c(findInterval(x = min(lidar_ALS_sample$X), vec = h1$breaks), findInterval(x = max(lidar_ALS_sample$X), vec = h1$breaks)),
        ylim=c(0, top), space=0, border='green', col = rgb(0.2, 0.9, 0.2, 0.2),
        main = paste0("Airborne lidar vs GEDI lidar - Footprint ", GEDI_FP_ID))
par(mar=c(5,1,0,1))
barplot(h2$counts, axes=F, xlim=c(0, top), 
        ylim = c(findInterval(x = min(lidar_ALS_sample$Z), vec = h2$breaks), findInterval(x = max(lidar_ALS_sample$Z), vec = h2$breaks)),
        space=0, border='green', col = rgb(0.2, 0.9, 0.2, 0.2), horiz=T)
par(mar=c(5,1,1,1))
plot(lidar_GEDI_wave$zBin~lidar_GEDI_wave$percEnergy, axes = T,
     xlim = c(0, 15),
     ylim = c(min(lidar_ALS_GEDI_FP@data$Z), max(lidar_ALS_GEDI_FP@data$Z)),
     type = 'l', col = "red", lwd = 2,

Part 6: Plotting Average GEDI waveforms

Plot the average waveform for this block of airborne lidar data
Extract all relative height metrics from the GEDI data

GEDI_All_RH = as.data.frame(t(lidar_GEDI_Bpts@data[ , grepl( "rhReal" , names( lidar_GEDI_Bpts@data ) ) ]))
GEDI_All_RHmean = as.data.frame(rowMeans(GEDI_All_RH))
colnames(GEDI_All_RHmean) = c("RH")
GEDI_All_RHmean$stdev = apply(GEDI_All_RH[,1:ncol(GEDI_All_RH)],1,sd)
GEDI_All_RHmean$binCuml = seq(0,100,2)
GEDI_All_RHmean$binPerc = 2
# Re-bin the relative height values into new bins
binsBig = seq(-100, 100, binSize)
rh = vector("numeric")
en = vector("numeric")
interv = vector("numeric")
for (i in 1:(nrow(GEDI_All_RHmean)-1)){
  start = length(rh)+1
  binsSmall = seq(GEDI_All_RHmean$RH[i], GEDI_All_RHmean$RH[i+1], 0.1)
  len = length(binsSmall)
  end = (start+len)-1
  rh[start:end] = binsSmall
  en[start:end] = 2/length(binsSmall)
  interv[start:end] = findInterval(x = rh[start:end], vec = binsBig)
}
# Combine the re-binned data into a data frame
lidar_GEDI_mean_preWave = data.frame(rh, en, interv)
lidar_GEDI_mean_preWave$binsBig = binsBig[interv]
lidar_GEDI_mean_wave = aggregate(lidar_GEDI_mean_preWave$en, by=list(Category=lidar_GEDI_mean_preWave$binsBig), FUN=sum)
colnames(lidar_GEDI_mean_wave) = c("zBin", "percEnergy")
# Make a plot of the average relative height values for this area
oldpar <- par()
par(mar=c(5,5,2,1))
layout(matrix(c(1,2),1,2,byrow=T),c(1,1), c(1,1))
plot(GEDI_All_RHmean$RH~GEDI_All_RHmean$binCuml, 
     main = "Mean GEDI RH Profile", type = 'l', lwd = 3,
     xlim = c(0,100), ylim = c(-2,50), xlab = "Cumulative Percent Energy",
     ylab = "Relative Height Above Ground (m)")
# Plot a polygon corresponding to 1 standard deviation around the RH profile
polyX = c(seq(0,100,2),rev(seq(0,100,2)))
polyY = c((GEDI_All_RHmean$RH-GEDI_All_RHmean$stdev), rev((GEDI_All_RHmean$RH+GEDI_All_RHmean$stdev)))
polygon(polyX, polyY, col = rgb(0.1,0.1,0.1,0.3), border = NA)
# Plot lines corresponding to different relative heights
RH25 = (GEDI_All_RHmean$RH[GEDI_All_RHmean$binCuml==24]+GEDI_All_RHmean$RH[GEDI_All_RHmean$binCuml==26])/2
lines(c(25,25), c(-10,RH25), lty = "dashed", type = 'l', col = "orange")
lines(c(-10,25), c(RH25,RH25), lty = "dashed", col = "orange")
text(10,RH25+2,"RH25")
HOME = GEDI_All_RHmean$RH[GEDI_All_RHmean$binCuml==50]
lines(c(50,50), c(-10,HOME), lty = "dashed", type = 'l', col = "green")
lines(c(-10,50), c(HOME,HOME), lty = "dashed", col = "green")
text(13,HOME+2,"H.O.M.E.")
RH75 = (GEDI_All_RHmean$RH[GEDI_All_RHmean$binCuml==74]+GEDI_All_RHmean$RH[GEDI_All_RHmean$binCuml==76])/2
lines(c(75,75), c(-10,RH75), lty = "dashed", type = 'l', col = "blue")
lines(c(-10,75), c(RH75,RH75), lty = "dashed", col = "blue")
text(10,RH75+2,"RH75")
RH98 = GEDI_All_RHmean$RH[GEDI_All_RHmean$binCuml==98]
lines(c(98,98), c(-10,RH98), lty = "dashed", type = 'l', col = "purple")
lines(c(-10,98), c(RH98,RH98), lty = "dashed", col = "purple")
text(10,RH98+2,"RH98")
# Make a plot of average waveform for this area
plot(lidar_GEDI_mean_wave$zBin~lidar_GEDI_mean_wave$percEnergy, 
     main = "Mean GEDI Waveform",
     xlab = "Percent Energy", ylab = "Height Above Ground (m)",
     xlim = c(0,10), ylim = c(-2,50), xaxs="i",
     type = 'l', lwd = 2, col = "red")
abline(h = RH25, lty = "dashed", col = "orange")
abline(h = HOME, lty = "dashed", col = "green")
abline(h = RH75, lty = "dashed", col = "blue")
abline(h = RH98, lty = "dashed", col = "purple")
